article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 55, Henderson St. 36
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Melvin Smith scored 13 points and Ryan Williams came off the bench to add 10 in Texas-San Antonio's 55-36 win over Henderson State on Wednesday night. The Roadrunners (3-4) held Henderson State scoreless for the first eight minutes and led 29-18 at halftime. The Reddies (4-3) scored the fewest points ever by a UTSA opponent, breaking the old record of 42 set in 1996. San Antonio turned 28 turnovers into 25 points and never trailed. Dee Dee Drake shot 6-of-8 from the field to lead the Reddies with 14 points. Larry Bray added nine points and grabbed five rebounds.
